# English-Only Code Rule

All code in this project must be written in English only:

- Variable names, function names, class names, and identifiers: English
- Code comments: English
- Console.log messages and debug output: English
- Commit messages: English
- File names: English

Exceptions (Hebrew is allowed):
- User-facing UI strings displayed to end users (button labels, error messages shown in the UI, placeholder text)
- Hebrew string enum values that are part of the data model (e.g. category values: 'לינה', 'הסעה', 'מזון', 'תרופות', 'ילדים', 'נפשי')
- Content inside PLANNING.md that describes the product for Hebrew-speaking stakeholders
